#: ../new/scripts.rst:4
msgid "Script Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:6
msgid ""
"See :doc:`Editor Support </new/editorsupport>` on how to use the new "
"Script Actions from map editors."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:10
msgid ":captiontag:`Gather at Enemy` (53)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:12
msgid ""
"The previously unused parameter of the :value:`Gather at Enemy` script "
"action is now added to :tag:`[General]AISafeDistance` to determine the "
"distance from the center of the enemy base the team should gather at. Can"
" be negative to shorten the distance."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:24
msgid ":captiontag:`Gather at Base` (54)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:26
msgid ""
":game:`Ares` splits the tag :tag:`[General]AISafeDistance` into two, "
"which is used for two similar team script actions serving different "
"purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:31
msgid ":tagdef:`[General]AIFriendlyDistance=integer - cells`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:30
msgid ""
"Cell distance the AI will use for gathering outside the owning player's "
"base using script action 54. Defaults to :tag:`[General]AISafeDistance`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:33
msgid ""
"Like for the :value:`Gather at Enemy` script action, the previously "
"unused parameter of the :value:`Gather at Base` script action is now "
"added to the distance from the center of the own base the team should "
"gather at. Can be negative to shorten the distance."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:47
msgid ":captiontag:`Iron Curtain` (55)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:49
msgid ""
"Previously, the game would only look at the first (and usually only) "
"super weapon with :tag:`Type=IronCurtain`, then check whether it was "
"either ready or almost charged. If that was not the case, the script "
"action failed."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:53
msgid ""
":game:`Ares` will instead check all super weapon with "
":tag:`SW.AITargetingMode=IronCurtain` and will fire the first one that is"
" fully charged, or wait, if any is at least almost charged. The script "
"will fail otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:58
msgid ""
"The previously unused parameter of the :value:`IronCurtain` script action"
" is now used to denote the group the Iron Curtain super weapon has to "
"belong to before being considered. This allows to create super weapon "
"groups (for instance for traditional Iron Curtain and new AttachEffect "
"boosts) and different teams to rely on different super weapon groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:71
msgid ":captiontag:`Auxiliary Power` (65)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:73
msgid ""
"This new script action permanently changes the power output of the house "
"owning the team. Power value can be negative to create a power drain. "
"Applying this effect multiple times is cumulative."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:77
msgid "The format is :value:`65,<power>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:86
msgid ":captiontag:`Kill Drivers` (66)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:88
msgid ""
"Kills all drivers of the units in this team. This script respects "
"Protected Drivers, Iron Curtain and all the other mechanisms that prevent"
" drivers being killed."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:92
msgid "All affected units will change to the country called :value:`Special`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:94
msgid "The format is :value:`66,0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:103
msgid ":captiontag:`Take Vehicles` (67)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:105
msgid ""
"All infantry in this team that are either :tag:`CanDrive=yes` or "
":tag:`VehicleThief=yes` will be assigned the closest vehicle they can "
"drive or hijack. If the infantry finds a vehicle to take, it will leave "
"the team."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:109
msgid ""
"This works like the similar script actions :value:`Garrison Structure`, "
":value:`Enter Occupiable`, and :value:`Enter Tank Bunker`: The infantry "
"will try to find a new object once the current one becomes unavailable "
"for capturing. If there is none such alternative object to take, the "
"infantry will stop."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:114
msgid "The format is :value:`67,0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:125
msgid ":captiontag:`Convert Type` (68)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:127
msgid ""
"Immediately changes all members of this team into their respective script"
" conversion types, if set. Units that don't have this tag set stay "
"unaffected. This is a generalization of the script actions :value:`Unload"
" Truck` and :value:`Load Truck`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:132
msgid ""
"See :ref:`Conversion Triggered by Team Script <convert-script>` for a "
"description of this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:135
msgid "The format is :value:`68,0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:144
msgid ":captiontag:`Sonar Reveal` (69)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:146
msgid ""
"Disables the ability of all team members to cloak themselves for a number"
" of frames defined by the second parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:149
msgid "Use :value:`0` to end the sonar effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:151
msgid "The format is :value:`69,<frames>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:160
msgid ":captiontag:`Disable Weapons` (70)"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:162
msgid ""
"Disables the ability of all team members to fire for a number of frames "
"defined by the second parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:165
msgid "Use :value:`0` to end the weapon disabling effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/scripts.rst:167
msgid "The format is :value:`70,<frames>`."
msgstr ""

